# IFRS 9 ECL Platform — Run 7 Spec (Full 8-Agent Exercise)

**Quality Target**: 9.0/10
**SME Mode**: Active (IFRS 9 / Basel III)
**Prior Run Score**: 9.05/10
**Approach**: Exercise ALL 8 harness agents. Improve design quality by refactoring remaining oversized files. Strengthen domain accuracy with SME-reviewed validation improvements.

## Sprint Plan

### Sprint 1: Refactor Large Frontend Files (Design Quality)
1. Split StressTesting.tsx (1022 lines) into focused sub-components (<200 lines each)
2. Split DataMapping.tsx (874 lines) into focused sub-components (<200 lines each)
3. Ensure zero regressions — all existing tests pass
4. Frontend builds cleanly with no TS errors
5. Visual QA: verify both pages render identically before/after refactoring

### Sprint 2: Refactor Large Backend Files (Design Quality)
1. Split reports.py (728 lines) into focused sub-modules
2. Split ecl_engine.py (638 lines) into focused sub-modules
3. Split hazard.py (634 lines) into focused sub-modules
4. Maintain backward compatibility via re-exports
5. All existing tests pass — zero regressions
6. Add 10+ new tests for refactored modules

### Sprint 3: Domain Accuracy Improvements (SME-Reviewed)
1. Add EAD boundary validation (non-negative) per IFRS 9.B5.5.31
2. Add LGD range enforcement [0, 1] per IFRS 9.B5.5.28
3. Add Stage 3 PD consistency check (PD should be near 1.0 for defaulted) per IFRS 9.B5.5.37
4. Add discount factor validation (EIR > -1)
5. Add 15+ new domain validation tests with SME-derived test scenarios
6. SME review of implementation before handoff

### Documentation Batch (after Sprint 3)
1. Documentation Agent: Update docs for refactored modules, capture screenshots
2. Installation Agent: Clean install test (rm -rf .venv && ./install.sh)
3. Integration Agent: Full regression sweep + cross-feature user journeys

### Final Integration Evaluation
All 8 agents participate. Must meet 9.0/10 quality target.
